    "pfs": "Limited",
    "aonid": 251,
    "game-obj": "Weapons",
    "stat_block": {
        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "weapon",
        "text": "The shobhad longrifle is a firearm with a long, rifled barrel. Often mounted with a multi-lensed scope for targeting at an array of ranges and a chambering mechanism that can adjust the speed and penetrating power of each shot, it's the preferred weapon of many shobhad warriors. Shobhad longrifles are equipped with a built-in silencer so they make no more noise than a crossbow when fired. A shobhad longrifle is a martial weapon.",
        "level": 1,
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Rare",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 137,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 11,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "e4b0e4f5f4b3d4cad3bea67ec077e297",
                "text": "This rarity indicates that a rules element is very difficult to find in the game world. A rare feat, spell, item or the like is available to players only if the GM decides to include it in the game, typically through discovery during play. Creatures with this trait are rare. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creatures is increased by 5.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 26
                    }
                ],
                "schema_version": 1.1,
                "classes": [
                    "rare"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Backstabber",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 172,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 282",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 282",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 282,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "36bd7375ee334ca30404dac02062c504",
                "text": "When you hit an off-guard creature, this weapon deals 1 precision damage in addition to its normal damage. The precision damage increases to 2 if the weapon is a _+3 weapon_.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "off-guard",
                        "alt": "off-guard",
                        "game-obj": "Conditions",
                        "aonid": 58
                    }
                ],
                "schema_version": 1.1,
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Concussive",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 401,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "NPC Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "NPC Core pg. 50",
                            "alt": "NPC Core pg. 50",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 236
                        },
                        "page": 50
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "e3ebabe03e8190448c5d613bf42a41d2",
                "text": "These weapons smash as much as puncture. When determining a creature's resistance or immunity to damage from this weapon, use the weaker of the target's resistance or immunity to piercing or to bludgeoning. For instance, if the creature were immune to piercing and had no resistance or immunity to bludgeoning damage, it would take full damage from a concussive weapon. Resistance or immunity to all physical damage, or all damage, applies as normal.",
                "schema_version": 1.1,
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Fatal",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 178,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 282",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 282",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 282,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "db3dcba30733bab63da3438275614311",
                "text": "The fatal trait includes a die size. On a critical hit, the weapon\u2019s damage die increases to that die size instead of the normal die size, and the weapon adds one additional damage die of the listed size.",
                "schema_version": 1.1,
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ],
                "value": "d12"
            },
            {
                "name": "Kickback",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 409,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "NPC Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "NPC Core pg. 50",
                            "alt": "NPC Core pg. 50",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 236
                        },
                        "page": 50
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "09b831753bf44bcef2c3a6a7a3c6f360",
                "text": "A kickback weapon is extra powerful and difficult to use due to its high recoil. A kickback weapon deals 1 additional damage with all attacks. Firing a kickback weapon gives a \u20132 circumstance penalty to the attack roll, but characters with +2 or more Strength ignore the penalty. Attaching a kickback weapon to a deployed bipod, tripod, or other stabilizer can lower or negate this penalty.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "tripod",
                        "alt": "tripod",
                        "game-obj": "Equipment",
                        "aonid": 1207
                    }
                ],
                "schema_version": 1.1,
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Volley",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 201,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 283",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 283",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 283,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "ea2a97c7c225653dc2f8c20abc1815aa",
                "text": "This ranged weapon is less effective at close distances. Your attacks against targets that are at a distance within the range listed take a \u20132 penalty.",
                "schema_version": 1.1,
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ],
                "value": "30 ft."
            }
        ],
